580
00:36:24,700 --> 00:36:27,130
Grandma slipped it to me all these years.

581
00:36:27,130 --> 00:36:28,700
I also helped classmates
write their homework

582
00:36:28,700 --> 00:36:29,960
and they paid me.

583
00:36:29,960 --> 00:36:32,000
Your grandma gave you money?

584
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:33,460
Your baby brother's shoes are so worn out.

585
00:36:33,460 --> 00:36:34,530
She doesn't bear to buy a new pair.

586
00:36:34,530 --> 00:36:35,460
How could she give you money?

587
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:37,700
Baby brother.

588
00:36:37,700 --> 00:36:39,360
All you talk about is him.

589
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:39,960
What about me?

590
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:41,660
Aren't I your kid?

591
00:36:41,660 --> 00:36:42,960
His shoes are worn out.

592
00:36:42,960 --> 00:36:43,960
What about me?

593
00:36:43,960 --> 00:36:46,300
My clothes and shoes are worn out too.

594
00:36:46,300 --> 00:36:47,960
Even since he's born,

595
00:36:47,960 --> 00:36:50,460
you never bought me new clothes.

596
00:36:50,460 --> 00:36:52,130
When the teacher asked what my dream was,

597
00:36:52,130 --> 00:36:53,600
I wouldn't dare to tell her.

598
00:36:53,600 --> 00:36:55,100
Because I don't deserve it.

599
00:36:55,100 --> 00:36:57,330
I just want to go to school
like other kids.

600
00:36:57,330 --> 00:36:59,100
Just like other kids.

601
00:36:59,100 --> 00:37:00,660
Why is it so hard?

602
00:37:00,660 --> 00:37:01,360
Right.

603
00:37:01,360 --> 00:37:02,500
You're right.

604
00:37:02,500 --> 00:37:03,530
You know you don't deserve it.

605
00:37:03,530 --> 00:37:04,960
What's with all the talking?

606
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:06,060
Starting tomorrow,

607
00:37:06,060 --> 00:37:07,560
write more homework for your classmates

608
00:37:07,560 --> 00:37:08,900
and give me all the money.

609
00:37:08,900 --> 00:37:10,300
You don't deserve it.

610
00:37:10,300 --> 00:37:11,260
Who are you talking to?

611
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:12,860
You.

612
00:37:13,500 --> 00:37:15,500
You don't deserve to be a mother.

613
00:37:15,500 --> 00:37:16,860
Check the calendar.

614
00:37:16,860 --> 00:37:18,360
What age do we live in?

615
00:37:18,360 --> 00:37:20,130
You still play the heavy gender bias game.

616
00:37:20,130 --> 00:37:21,300
As a mother,

617
00:37:21,300 --> 00:37:23,460
you can't even respect her.

618
00:37:23,460 --> 00:37:26,360
All she wants is living like other kids.

619
00:37:26,360 --> 00:37:28,060
But in front of her own mother,

620
00:37:28,060 --> 00:37:29,330
she don't even have

621
00:37:29,330 --> 00:37:30,500
the right

622
00:37:30,500 --> 00:37:32,130
to enjoy equal respect like other kids.

623
00:37:50,900 --> 00:37:51,420
Good morning.

624
00:38:02,060 --> 00:38:03,860
We've been an old couple.

625
00:38:03,880 --> 00:38:04,820
Don't do this.

626
00:38:06,550 --> 00:38:08,320
That's more reason we should do it.

627
00:38:12,420 --> 00:38:13,060
Honey,

628
00:38:15,720 --> 00:38:17,180
thanks for letting me home.

629
00:38:21,820 --> 00:38:22,700
Thanks for the flower.

630
00:38:24,800 --> 00:38:26,170
We're going to a movie,

631
00:38:26,170 --> 00:38:27,070
an exhibition,

632
00:38:27,070 --> 00:38:28,870
and a candlelight dinner.

633
00:38:28,870 --> 00:38:31,130
The time's actually pretty tight,

634
00:38:31,130 --> 00:38:33,030
because you have to freshen up
and put on makeup.

635
00:38:33,030 --> 00:38:34,570
It takes a while to get ready,

636
00:38:34,570 --> 00:38:34,970
right?

637
00:38:42,030 --> 00:38:43,600
Ms. Chen, I'm here to collect the key.

638
00:38:44,830 --> 00:38:45,230
Ms. Chen...

639
00:38:51,430 --> 00:38:51,970
Ms. Chen...

640
00:38:53,570 --> 00:38:54,400
Ms. Chen.

641
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:55,270
I'm here to collect the key.

642
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:14,560
♪Hush♪

643
00:39:15,960 --> 00:39:17,120
♪Don't wake him up yet♪

644
00:39:17,120 --> 00:39:18,680
♪This show is too good to miss♪

645
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:21,040
♪All the false affection is
incredibly cheap to me♪

646
00:39:21,040 --> 00:39:21,800
♪You make up lies♪

647
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:23,160
♪But I won't make a fool of myself♪

648
00:39:23,160 --> 00:39:23,840
♪Just be glad♪

649
00:39:23,840 --> 00:39:24,760
♪We can't be lovers♪

650
00:39:24,760 --> 00:39:25,960
♪Yet we get to stay foes♪

651
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:28,040
♪The changes in life are unpredictable♪

652
00:39:28,040 --> 00:39:30,840
♪All that's stable is more likely
to collapse♪

653
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:33,080
♪You're good at inventing games
and I'm good at playing♪

654
00:39:33,080 --> 00:39:35,840
♪Take it as the sweetest gift♪

655
00:39:35,880 --> 00:39:37,920
♪Honey, don't be afraid♪

656
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:39,240
♪Have you watched the fireworks show?♪

657
00:39:39,240 --> 00:39:40,880
♪Nothing is left after the dazzling♪

658
00:39:40,880 --> 00:39:41,720
♪The breathtaking view♪

659
00:39:41,720 --> 00:39:43,520
♪No one wants to tell
if it's real or an illusion♪

660
00:39:43,520 --> 00:39:45,880
♪Like how flowers bloom
on the most dangerous path♪

661
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:48,000
♪There will be deviations no matter
how thoughtful the plan is♪

662
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:50,480
♪All the self-imagined invincible
experiences are a joke♪

663
00:39:50,480 --> 00:39:51,680
♪You have your feet in two boats♪

664
00:39:51,680 --> 00:39:52,920
♪Why not take a look under your feet♪

665
00:39:53,080 --> 00:39:55,200
♪Is there the river of love
or bottomless cliff?♪

666
00:39:55,200 --> 00:39:59,120
♪Drowning in faded dreams♪

667
00:39:59,640 --> 00:40:05,000
♪Trying to have a clear look at myself♪

668
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:09,040
♪How many times
I've considered forgiving you♪

669
00:40:09,600 --> 00:40:14,840
♪That's how many times I come to senses♪

670
00:40:14,840 --> 00:40:18,840
♪The tranquility before the storm strikes♪

671
00:40:19,440 --> 00:40:24,760
♪I put myself back together
after being broken to pieces♪

672
00:40:24,760 --> 00:40:28,800
♪Not a stranger
to the tenderness in your eyes♪

673
00:40:29,320 --> 00:40:35,960
♪But a stranger to you♪

674
00:40:41,740 --> 00:40:46,580
[We All Lie]
